# Muscular System

> The human body has over **600 skeletal muscles**. Muscles work by attaching to bones via tendons — contracting to produce movement at joints.

## 📌 Key Concepts
- **Origin** — The fixed, proximal attachment point of a muscle
- **Insertion** — The movable, distal attachment point
- **Action** — The movement produced by contraction
- **Innervation** — The nerve supplying the muscle
- **Agonist / Antagonist** — Muscles working together or in opposition

## 🗂️ Muscles by Region

### Head & Neck
- [[Sternocleidomastoid]] — Neck flexion & rotation
- [[Masseter]] — Jaw closing (mastication)

### Trunk
- [[Pectoralis Major]] — Shoulder flexion, adduction, internal rotation
- [[Trapezius]] — Scapular elevation, retraction, depression
- [[Latissimus Dorsi]] — Shoulder extension, adduction, internal rotation
- [[Erector Spinae]] — Spinal extension and postural support
- [[Rectus Abdominis]] — Trunk flexion, abdominal compression

### Upper Limb
- [[Deltoid]] — Shoulder abduction
- [[Rotator Cuff]] — Shoulder stability (SITS muscles)
- [[Biceps Brachii]] — Elbow flexion & forearm supination
- [[Triceps Brachii]] — Elbow extension

### Lower Limb
- [[Iliopsoas]] — Hip flexion
- [[Gluteus Maximus]] — Hip extension
- [[Gluteus Medius]] — Hip abduction
- [[Quadriceps Femoris]] — Knee extension
- [[Hamstrings]] — Knee flexion & hip extension
- [[Gastrocnemius]] — Plantarflexion & knee flexion
- [[Tibialis Anterior]] — Dorsiflexion & foot inversion

